ZH: 不速之客是指没有受邀请却突然出现的人。
EN: "不速之客" refers to someone who appears suddenly without being invited.

ZH: 这个爬山活动的不速之客给我们带来了惊喜。
EN: The unexpected guest on this hiking trip brought us a pleasant surprise.

ZH: 他是个不速之客，我们并不欢迎他的到来。
EN: He is an uninvited guest, we do not welcome his arrival.

ZH: 这个老朋友突然到访，像个不速之客一样出现。
EN: This old friend suddenly visited, appearing like an unexpected guest.

ZH: 不速之客总是让人感到不安。
EN: Unexpected guests always make people feel uneasy.

ZH: 我们正在享受家庭聚会时，来了一个不速之客。
EN: We were enjoying a family gathering when an uninvited guest arrived.

ZH: 他带着一位不速之客来参加了我的生日派对。
EN: He brought an unexpected guest to my birthday party.

ZH: 这位不速之客似乎很高兴参加这个活动。
EN: This unexpected guest seems to be happy to participate in this event.

ZH: 我们刚坐下的时候，就出现了一个不速之客。
EN: An unexpected guest appeared just as we sat down.

ZH: 这个不速之客让整个晚会的气氛变得尴尬。
EN: This unexpected guest made the atmosphere of the entire party awkward.

ZH: 她突然打开门走进来，像个不速之客。
EN: She suddenly opened the door and walked in like an unexpected guest.

ZH: 不速之客突然出现，打破了大家的安宁。
EN: The unexpected guest suddenly appeared, disrupting everyone's peace.

ZH: 派对正在进行时，不速之客装作很熟悉的样子加入了我们。
EN: The party was in progress when the unexpected guest joined us, pretending to be familiar.

ZH: 我们惊讶地看着不速之客悄悄离开了。
EN: We watched in surprise as the unexpected guest quietly left.

ZH: 他宛如不速之客般闯进了我们的对话。
EN: He barged into our conversation like an unexpected guest.

ZH: 这位不速之客带了一些礼物，让我们稍微感到欣慰。
EN: This unexpected guest brought some gifts, making us feel somewhat comforted.

ZH: 不速之客的到来给我们的计划带来了一些麻烦。
EN: The arrival of the unexpected guest caused some trouble to our plans.

ZH: 被认为是不速之客的人，常常在别人的过程中冒然出现。
EN: People considered as unexpected guests often appear abruptly in other people's affairs.

ZH: 这位不速之客谦虚地向大家自我介绍。
EN: The unexpected guest humbly introduced themselves to everyone.

ZH: 大家都没有注意到那个不速之客的离开。
EN: No one noticed the departure of the unexpected guest.
